# SDD Step 4 — Analyze Cross-Artifact Consistency

Review your spec and your plan using the checklist below.
Spec excerpt:
> some spec content

Plan excerpt:
> plan.md content — patterns selected, layers mapped, user stories covered. plan.md content — patterns selected, layers mapped, user stories covered. plan.md content — patterns selected, layers mapped, user stories covered. plan.md content — patterns selected, layers mapped, user stories covered.

## Consistency Checks
- [ ] Every User Story in spec.md has a corresponding section in plan.md
- [ ] Every Acceptance Criteria has a testable implementation path in plan.md
- [ ] All [NEEDS CLARIFICATION] markers are resolved (zero remaining)
- [ ] plan.md references at least: #1 (Entity), #3 (Use Case), #4 (Repository Port), #6 (UI State), #7 (ViewModel), #9 (Navigation), #11 (Result/Railway), #16 (Repository Adapter)
- [ ] contracts/navigation.md covers all screens implied by the user stories
- [ ] data-model.md covers all entities and local storage implied by the spec

## Architecture Gates
- [ ] Domain layer has zero external dependencies planned
- [ ] Use Cases only use domain entities and repository ports
- [ ] Data layer only implements domain ports (no UI/ViewModel references)
- [ ] Composition Root is planned in main.*

## Mobile-Specific Pattern Coverage
- [ ] If spec mentions "offline" or "no network" → plan includes Offline-First (#17) and Local Data Source (#15)
- [ ] If spec mentions "auth" or "login" → plan includes Auth Interceptor (#19) and Secure Storage (#20)
- [ ] If spec mentions "push" or "notification" → plan includes Push Notifications (#22)
- [ ] If spec mentions "deep link" or "share" → plan includes Deep Linking (#24)
- [ ] If spec mentions "background sync" → plan includes Background Job (#25)
- [ ] If spec mentions "biometric" → plan includes Biometric Auth (#23)
- [ ] If spec mentions "experiment" or "flag" → plan includes Feature Flag (#21)

## Output format
```md
## Analysis Report

### ✅ Passed Checks
- [list]

### ❌ Critical Inconsistencies (MUST fix before spec_tasks)
- CI-01: [description]

### ⚠️ Warnings (should fix before implementing)
- W-01: [description]

### Gate Result
[PASS: Call spec_tasks] OR [FAIL: Fix CI-XX items first, then re-run spec_analyze]
```
